1
00:00:00,733 --> 00:00:04,300
- [EXPLOSION]
- [SCREAMING]

2
00:00:04,300 --> 00:00:06,433
<i> - Cheska? Trixie?
</i>- [COUGHING]

3
00:00:06,433 --> 00:00:07,667
<i> Gio!</i>

4
00:00:07,667 --> 00:00:10,033
<i> You've ruined our families!</i>

5
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:12,400
<i>I would do anything
for the treasure!</i>

6
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,067
- [GUNSHOT]
- [JADE SCREAMS] Martin!

7
00:00:14,067 --> 00:00:16,200
<i>- Martin! Martin!
- Martin!</i>

8
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:18,233
<i>You've been blinded
by your greed.</i>

9
00:00:18,233 --> 00:00:20,433
Treasure can be found anywhere,

10
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:22,733
<i> but not family!</i>

11
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:24,033
<i> Get Jade.</i>

12
00:00:24,033 --> 00:00:25,400
<i> - No!
- No! Wait!</i>

13
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:26,767
<i>- Edward!
- Kiko!</i>

14
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:28,033
<i> Kiko!</i>

15
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:30,233
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

16
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:31,733
<i> Kiko!</i>

17
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:34,433
<i>- Kiko, hold on!
- Kiko!</i>

18
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:35,467
<i> Kiko!</i>

19
00:00:35,467 --> 00:00:37,067
<i> Hang on!</i>

20
00:00:37,067 --> 00:00:38,700
<i> Kiko!</i>

21
00:00:39,767 --> 00:00:41,033
<i> Kiko!</i>

22
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:44,800
[LIGHTHEARTED MUSIC PLAYING]

23
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:46,633
Oh! Kiko is here!

24
00:00:46,633 --> 00:00:47,700
He's here.

25
00:00:47,700 --> 00:00:49,733
Sir Martin! Sir Kiko is here!

26
00:01:04,467 --> 00:01:05,467
Bro...

27
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:07,233
Welcome home.

28
00:01:08,767 --> 00:01:15,733
[LIGHTHEARTED MUSIC CONTINUES]

29
00:01:22,267 --> 00:01:23,300
Is that okay?

30
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:25,167
Yeah.

31
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:29,233
Come on.

32
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,300
Shall we?

33
00:01:33,333 --> 00:01:34,733
- [RAPHIE] Ladies first?
- [SARI CHUCKLES]

34
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:38,033
[SIGHS]

35
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,267
Thank you everyone for coming.

36
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,100
As you all know,

37
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:45,467
Easter Sundays are very special
for our families.

38
00:01:45,867 --> 00:01:48,733
That was the only time
we could visit Papa.

39
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,800
And Easter egg hunting

40
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:53,433
was the highlight
of our vacations.

41
00:01:54,567 --> 00:01:56,833
That was one of Kiko's
most favorite activities.

42
00:01:57,367 --> 00:02:02,733
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:02:03,567 --> 00:02:06,300
But, for some reason,

44
00:02:07,267 --> 00:02:09,567
he would never find
the golden egg.

45
00:02:11,567 --> 00:02:13,333
[GIO] We'd tell him

46
00:02:14,333 --> 00:02:16,733
that only brave boys
can find the golden egg.

47
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:20,633
Kiko might've never found one,

48
00:02:23,133 --> 00:02:25,133
but he's still the bravest
out of us three.

49
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:33,433
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

50
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:38,567
So for the first
Easter celebration

51
00:02:38,567 --> 00:02:40,267
since the hotel opened,

52
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,567
let's celebrate Kiko with...

53
00:02:42,567 --> 00:02:44,500
an Easter egg hunt!

54
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:46,833
- Yes!
- [ALL CLAPPING]

55
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:47,867
- Oh, yes!
- Let's go!

56
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:49,533
Shall we go?

57
00:02:49,533 --> 00:02:50,667
Come on, let's hunt!

58
00:02:50,667 --> 00:02:52,667
- [JUSTIN] Let's go!
- [RAPHIE] Miss Jade, come on.

59
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:54,933
I saw one over here. Let's go!

60
00:02:54,933 --> 00:02:56,433
Miss Jade, come on!

61
00:03:03,633 --> 00:03:10,600
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

62
00:04:03,667 --> 00:04:04,867
Come on, Cheska.

63
00:04:05,367 --> 00:04:06,767
We're finally about
to open the bar

64
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:08,967
and you're leaving now?

65
00:04:08,967 --> 00:04:12,267
[CHUCKLES] Girlie,
I'm not gonna leave you.

66
00:04:12,867 --> 00:04:14,600
I'm just not
gonna be your manager.

67
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:16,233
But why?

68
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,767
We've been
working hard for this.

69
00:04:19,433 --> 00:04:20,267
[TONGUE CLICKS]

70
00:04:20,267 --> 00:04:22,600
Well, it's your
personal project.

71
00:04:23,967 --> 00:04:26,300
I kind of want to...

72
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:28,600
have my own personal project.

73
00:04:28,633 --> 00:04:30,500
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

74
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,967
I really want to start
that vegetable garden.

75
00:04:33,667 --> 00:04:35,767
It's been my dream
that we get our own

76
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:38,233
our own small farm.

77
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:41,467
And also...

78
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:45,300
So, I can show

79
00:04:46,267 --> 00:04:47,233
Kiko...

80
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,633
that even though he's gone,

81
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,300
we can still have a good life
on our own.

82
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:59,400
[TONGUE CLICKS]

83
00:05:02,900 --> 00:05:03,967
Besides...

84
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:07,333
I think it's time that you...

85
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:10,900
have a real partner.

86
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,300
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

87
00:05:18,033 --> 00:05:20,267
Come on,
let's go find easter eggs.

88
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:22,867
[TRIXIE] Justin.

89
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,400
Cheska is going to leave me.

90
00:05:25,967 --> 00:05:26,933
Huh?

91
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,433
How about the bar?

92
00:05:29,433 --> 00:05:31,033
I'm not! Stop that.

93
00:05:31,567 --> 00:05:33,400
I told you,
I'm not leaving you.

94
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,467
[INHALES]

95
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:36,400
We're still friends.

96
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:39,567
You're my only girlie friend.

97
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:43,867
We just need to focus on...

98
00:05:45,067 --> 00:05:47,733
our own personal projects.

99
00:05:51,967 --> 00:05:53,300
Well, then...

100
00:05:54,867 --> 00:05:57,833
I'm going on a solo trip
for this egg hunt.

101
00:05:57,833 --> 00:05:58,933
[CHUCKLES]

102
00:05:58,933 --> 00:06:00,900
You keep that bucket.

103
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:03,433
Of course!

104
00:06:03,433 --> 00:06:04,567
Let's do a group hug!

105
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:08,000
[CHESKA SNIFFLES]

106
00:06:08,867 --> 00:06:15,800
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

107
00:06:22,567 --> 00:06:23,867
I got you, bro.

108
00:06:29,133 --> 00:06:30,467
[SIGHS HAPPILY]

109
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,500
Since your manager just left...

110
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,067
can I apply for the position?

111
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:37,767
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

112
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:39,333
Justin Almazan.

113
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:41,033
At your service.

114
00:06:43,467 --> 00:06:44,700
What about...

115
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:45,733
partner?

116
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:49,600
I would love to.

117
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:53,467
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

118
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,800
Well?

119
00:06:55,733 --> 00:06:57,133
Shall we go look
for Easter eggs...

120
00:06:58,733 --> 00:06:59,800
partner?

121
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:02,433
Partner.

122
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:12,767
[MUSIC FADES]

123
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:23,167
[SIGHS]

124
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:30,800
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

125
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,800
[KIKO] My happy memory...

126
00:07:45,933 --> 00:07:48,500
<i> is meeting my best friend.</i>

127
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,633
<i> Thank you, universe!</i>

128
00:07:56,133 --> 00:07:59,067
Thank you! Thank you, universe!

129
00:07:59,067 --> 00:08:00,633
<i> Yeah!</i>

130
00:08:00,633 --> 00:08:01,833
[JADE SIGHS DEEPLY]

131
00:08:03,467 --> 00:08:04,433
<i> Jade.</i>

132
00:08:05,767 --> 00:08:07,467
<i> Will you be my...</i>

133
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:09,867
<i> best friend again?</i>

134
00:08:09,867 --> 00:08:12,500
<i> Hmm... yes.</i>

135
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:13,800
[KIKO] That's settled, then.

136
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:16,700
<i>We'll stick together,
whatever happens.</i>

137
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:19,467
[JADE]
We'll stick together, I promise.

138
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:21,933
- [KIKO]<i> We'll stick together.
</i>- [JADE] I promise.

139
00:08:24,267 --> 00:08:25,800
<i> We'll stick together.</i>

140
00:08:30,067 --> 00:08:32,900
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

141
00:08:33,867 --> 00:08:40,833
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

142
00:08:48,867 --> 00:08:55,833
[SOFT, DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

143
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:11,567
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:22,900
I found the golden egg, Kiko.

145
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:35,000
[KIKO] I chose
to love you in silence...

146
00:09:36,967 --> 00:09:39,933
<i>because you're more important
than my feelings.</i>

147
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:45,867
<i>I hope nothing changes
between us.</i>

148
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:50,300
Nothing's gonna change, Kiko.

149
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,167
[VOICE CRACKS]
You will always be...

150
00:09:56,133 --> 00:09:57,800
my best friend.

151
00:09:58,867 --> 00:10:05,833
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

152
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,767
[SNIFFLES, EXHALES]

153
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,667
[CRIES SOFTLY]

154
00:10:28,933 --> 00:10:30,333
[GIO] Fix it properly.
It's crooked!

155
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:31,700
I'm on it. Hang on.

156
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:32,733
Let me finish.

157
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:38,367
There.

158
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:41,800
[MARTIN SIGHS]

159
00:10:43,433 --> 00:10:45,400
[GIO] I think that's the most
complete group photo we have.

160
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:50,633
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

161
00:10:50,633 --> 00:10:52,100
[MARTIN] He's part of the hotel.

162
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,467
I'll never forget you, bro.

163
00:10:58,267 --> 00:10:59,533
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

164
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:02,367
This one.

165
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,567
Of course,
we can't leave this out.

166
00:11:04,567 --> 00:11:10,800
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

167
00:11:10,833 --> 00:11:12,600
[HAMMER CLACKING]

168
00:11:24,133 --> 00:11:26,300
[KIKO]<i> This is a promise
</i> that no matter what happens,

169
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:28,267
<i> I'll always be Gio's Kiko.</i>

170
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:32,367
<i> I'll always be Martin's Kiko.</i>

171
00:11:34,467 --> 00:11:37,200
[MARTIN]<i> You said
</i> you'd never leave us.

172
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:42,600
[GIO] We'll keep fighting
for a peaceful life.

173
00:11:43,667 --> 00:11:45,633
[MARTIN]<i> So our families
</i> can be safe.

174
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:48,600
[GIO]<i> For justice
</i> for our father.

175
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,200
[KIKO] So...

176
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,733
<i>...the fear in our hearts
will finally be gone.</i>

177
00:11:56,867 --> 00:11:58,200
[GIO] Strong man.

178
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,233
[MARTIN SNICKERS]

179
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,433
Say hi to Papa for us, okay?

180
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:09,467
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

181
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:15,400
Is there still a lot left?

182
00:12:15,433 --> 00:12:16,567
Just a little more.

183
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:18,367
Okay, I'll help you.

184
00:12:18,367 --> 00:12:19,967
- Just wipe these down.
- [PLATES CLATTERING]

185
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:21,700
Thank you.

186
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,367
I heard you're leaving too?

187
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,167
Mh-mm.

188
00:12:28,167 --> 00:12:30,300
This is my last shift
here at the hotel.

189
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:32,300
Tomorrow,

190
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:34,333
I'll be reporting to school.

191
00:12:35,233 --> 00:12:37,900
[PLATES CLATTERING]

192
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:40,867
Wow, it's like...

193
00:12:41,367 --> 00:12:43,767
I can't imagine this hotel
without you.

194
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:47,500
Well, this has always been
a big part of my life.

195
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,567
But...

196
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,467
I guess it's time.

197
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:53,333
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

198
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:55,900
It's time to chase my dreams.

199
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:58,500
To become a designer!

200
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:01,400
[MOUTH CLICKS] For Monette.

201
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:05,500
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

202
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,333
- [PLATES CLATTERING]
- [SIGHS]

203
00:13:07,933 --> 00:13:09,200
Wow.

204
00:13:10,300 --> 00:13:11,800
You know, I'm sure...

205
00:13:12,567 --> 00:13:13,633
[MOUTH CLICKS]

206
00:13:13,633 --> 00:13:15,467
Monette is so proud of you.

207
00:13:16,433 --> 00:13:17,833
Wherever she is now.

208
00:13:18,633 --> 00:13:22,333
Hey, don't forget us
once you're famous, okay?

209
00:13:22,367 --> 00:13:23,600
Of course! [CHUCKLES]

210
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,867
There's no way

211
00:13:24,867 --> 00:13:27,633
I'd ever forget everyone
I met here at the hotel.

212
00:13:27,633 --> 00:13:32,733
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

213
00:13:32,733 --> 00:13:35,533
As long as Monette
lives in my heart...

214
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:41,367
Hotel 88 will always
be a part of me.

215
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:47,367
Oh, please.

216
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:49,767
You're just going to miss me.

217
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:51,967
- Admit it.
- So much, sis! Seriously!

218
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:59,433
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

219
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,333
You were the one who found it.

220
00:14:06,633 --> 00:14:07,900
For Kiko.

221
00:14:12,567 --> 00:14:14,000
Kiko was a good man.

222
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:16,933
He saved you.

223
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,733
This is my going-away gift.

224
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:26,700
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:28,500
I talked to Luna last week.

226
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:32,567
She said you and your mom
are staying in Spain for now.

227
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:39,400
I'm going there
to be with Mom first.

228
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:42,000
Or I guess...

229
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,767
she's the one coming with me.

230
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:47,833
I found an art school there.

231
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:51,100
I'll see if I can get in.

232
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:56,467
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

233
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:57,400
[EXHALES]

234
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:59,433
Are you staying there for good?

235
00:15:02,533 --> 00:15:03,867
I don't know.

236
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,533
Honestly,

237
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:07,933
after everything
that's happened,

238
00:15:07,933 --> 00:15:09,367
I don't know anymore.

239
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:15,400
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

240
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:16,400
Jade...

241
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:18,700
First, Dad.

242
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:20,833
Then Leon.

243
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:23,700
Then Kiko.

244
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:28,867
Losing that many people
was not in my bingo card.

245
00:15:29,733 --> 00:15:31,067
So, I guess... [EXHALES]

246
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:34,100
my time in Spain
will help me figure out

247
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:36,600
what I really want
out of my life.

248
00:15:36,933 --> 00:15:41,833
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:43,967
If you leave...

250
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:48,433
I might lose you again.

251
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,033
If I don't leave...

252
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,700
I might lose myself.

253
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,833
I need time to heal.

254
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:04,400
Just like you do.

255
00:16:05,533 --> 00:16:07,100
You were close to Mister Andy.

256
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,400
I'm sure...

257
00:16:09,767 --> 00:16:11,833
I'm sure you need time
to heal, too.

258
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:16,567
[SNIFFLES]

259
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,800
[BREATH QUIVERS]

260
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:22,533
Edward...

261
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:25,133
When we first grew apart,

262
00:16:25,967 --> 00:16:28,167
fate found a way
to let us meet again.

263
00:16:29,033 --> 00:16:30,533
Who knows?

264
00:16:31,667 --> 00:16:33,667
This time...

265
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,833
fate might do the same.

266
00:16:37,767 --> 00:16:45,500
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

267
00:16:48,633 --> 00:16:51,667
What's this
going away gift of yours?

268
00:16:54,767 --> 00:16:55,767
Open it.

269
00:16:59,767 --> 00:17:06,700
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

270
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,467
It's my favorite.

271
00:17:17,633 --> 00:17:18,767
Thank you.

272
00:17:32,733 --> 00:17:33,933
Goodbye, Jade.

273
00:17:37,633 --> 00:17:38,633
[INHALES]

274
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:50,067
Thank you, Edward.

275
00:17:54,033 --> 00:17:55,733
I'm going to miss you.

276
00:17:57,933 --> 00:17:59,833
You'll always be a part of me.

277
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:07,233
You will always be...

278
00:18:07,967 --> 00:18:09,600
my Eddybear.

279
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:17,567
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

280
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:40,200
- [SKIDS]
- [GIO] What?

281
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:41,267
Same old deal?

282
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:42,333
The one who goes last
has poop on their butt.

283
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:43,300
Wow!

284
00:18:43,733 --> 00:18:45,233
So mature, brother!

285
00:18:46,133 --> 00:18:47,133
[MARTIN LAUGHS]

286
00:18:47,133 --> 00:18:48,867
"Brother"? Stop it!

287
00:18:49,233 --> 00:18:50,367
Fine!

288
00:18:50,367 --> 00:18:51,867
If you don't like "brother",
then bro.

289
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:54,267
Bro?

290
00:18:56,467 --> 00:18:57,400
Bro.

291
00:18:58,267 --> 00:18:59,833
Okay!

292
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:01,467
The one who goes last
has poop on their butt, bro!

293
00:19:01,467 --> 00:19:02,433
[MARTIN] You're on!

294
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:08,067
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

295
00:19:08,067 --> 00:19:11,367
[BIKE ROLLING]

296
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:16,400
[MARTIN GRUNTS]

297
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:19,233
[GIO] There they are!

298
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:21,867
Oh!

299
00:19:21,867 --> 00:19:24,933
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

300
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:26,700
[LUNA AND SARI CHUCKLING]

301
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:33,933
[MARTIN GROANS]

302
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:39,933
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

303
00:19:39,933 --> 00:19:41,800
[SARI AND MARTIN CHUCKLING]

304
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:46,467
Come on.

305
00:19:49,767 --> 00:19:51,233
[MARTIN] What are we doing here?

306
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:53,400
[SARI] Grandpa told me,

307
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:55,933
this is where you can see
the most beautiful golden light

308
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:57,067
on the entire island.

309
00:19:58,233 --> 00:19:59,100
[MARTIN] There it is.

310
00:19:59,467 --> 00:20:00,700
[SARI] Beautiful, right?

311
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,400
[MARTIN EXHALES]

312
00:20:04,033 --> 00:20:05,100
[MARTIN] Wow.

313
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,900
But...

314
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:14,067
I have something even better
to show you.

315
00:20:14,433 --> 00:20:15,800
Really, sir?

316
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:16,933
- Something better...
- Mh-mm.

317
00:20:16,933 --> 00:20:18,767
...than that golden light?

318
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:22,033
Sari.

319
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:24,000
Close your eyes.

320
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,000
Huh?

321
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:26,800
You said you'd show me
something,

322
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:27,833
then now I have to close
my eyes?

323
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:28,900
Just do it.

324
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:31,833
[SIGHS]

325
00:20:32,133 --> 00:20:33,800
Sir, don't joke around.

326
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:36,800
[SARI] Sir, is it going
to take long?

327
00:20:37,467 --> 00:20:38,933
[MARTIN] Open your eyes.

328
00:20:38,933 --> 00:20:42,500
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

329
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:43,833
Heart fold?

330
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:45,400
You know how to do
a heart fold?

331
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,400
[EXHALES]

332
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,100
I learned to have a heart...

333
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:51,233
because of you.

334
00:20:54,300 --> 00:20:55,833
Growing up,

335
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:59,933
all I did was try to please
my stepdad and my family.

336
00:21:00,967 --> 00:21:02,300
Because back then,
I felt like...

337
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:06,367
I'd only have value
if they accepted me.

338
00:21:09,067 --> 00:21:11,900
But ever since I stayed
at Hotel 88...

339
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:14,067
ever since I met you...

340
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:16,400
and stayed with you...

341
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:23,867
you accepted me

342
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:27,200
for who I am.

343
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:30,500
Whether I have value or not.

344
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:35,567
That's the moment
I found my heart.

345
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:41,100
Sir,

346
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:44,433
even if you're not the one
the universe gave me,

347
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:47,867
I would still choose you.

348
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,133
You are my heart, Sari.

349
00:21:54,567 --> 00:21:56,200
I heart you too, sir.

350
00:21:58,067 --> 00:21:59,167
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

351
00:22:01,067 --> 00:22:08,033
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

352
00:22:18,667 --> 00:22:25,600
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

353
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:26,900
- Sir...
- [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

354
00:22:28,633 --> 00:22:30,200
I mean...

355
00:22:32,333 --> 00:22:34,100
I love you too, Martin.

356
00:22:37,667 --> 00:22:39,433
[CHUCKLING SOFTLY]

357
00:22:39,433 --> 00:22:44,667
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

358
00:22:44,667 --> 00:22:47,100
[SARI GASPS] Universe!

359
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:50,433
I'm not going to be alone
anymore!

360
00:22:50,467 --> 00:22:51,633
[BOTH LAUGHING]

361
00:22:51,633 --> 00:22:54,533
My heart finally
has someone with it!

362
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:59,467
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

363
00:22:59,467 --> 00:23:00,633
[LUNA] Thank you, Gio.

364
00:23:02,033 --> 00:23:03,033
[GIO] For what?

365
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:06,333
Because you didn't
give up on me.

366
00:23:09,433 --> 00:23:11,367
What's important is that
you came back to me.

367
00:23:17,067 --> 00:23:20,400
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

368
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:21,667
[LUNA] This is a promise ring.

369
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:26,967
A promise that I will never
turn my back on you

370
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:29,533
and leave you again.

371
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:35,333
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

372
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:36,933
You won't turn your back
on me anymore?

373
00:23:38,533 --> 00:23:39,667
Not anymore.

374
00:23:40,733 --> 00:23:42,233
You're not going
to leave me anymore?

375
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,100
No.

376
00:23:44,100 --> 00:23:48,467
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

377
00:23:48,467 --> 00:23:50,500
Then...

378
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:55,967
let's spend the rest
of our lives together.

379
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:59,367
["TADHANA" BY
SOFRONIO VASQUEZ PLAYING]

380
00:24:00,367 --> 00:24:02,133
[INHALES DEEPLY]

381
00:24:02,133 --> 00:24:03,300
Yes.

382
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:06,200
Let's spend the rest
of our lives together.

383
00:24:19,300 --> 00:24:26,233
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

384
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:48,133
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

385
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:09,067
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

386
00:25:10,067 --> 00:25:12,800
[MARTIN] Oh, my god!

387
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:15,433
Congrats, bro.

388
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:19,800
I'm happy for you guys.

389
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,200
[LUNA] You, too!

390
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:23,200
[MARTIN] Thank you.

391
00:25:23,767 --> 00:25:25,367
[CHUCKLING]

392
00:25:25,767 --> 00:25:32,733
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

393
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:37,600
[TABLEWARE CLINKING]

394
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:38,567
Thank you.

395
00:25:39,567 --> 00:25:40,667
[CLEARS THROAT LOUDLY]

396
00:25:40,667 --> 00:25:42,367
Oh! Sorry.

397
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:45,300
[GIGGLES]

398
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:46,733
At least, ask me first.

399
00:25:47,733 --> 00:25:49,067
Yes, big bro.

400
00:25:49,267 --> 00:25:50,467
[SARI] Martin.

401
00:25:50,667 --> 00:25:52,767
Stop being so strict
with sissy.

402
00:25:53,633 --> 00:25:54,633
"Sissy?!"

403
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:56,367
"Martin?!"

404
00:25:56,367 --> 00:25:57,567
You've dropped the "sir"?

405
00:25:57,567 --> 00:25:58,533
Yes, I have!

406
00:25:58,533 --> 00:25:59,433
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

407
00:25:59,433 --> 00:26:02,300
Sari, I leave my brother
in your care.

408
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:03,600
[SARI] Thank you, sissy!

409
00:26:04,433 --> 00:26:06,367
[RAPHIE] What a surprise, Sari!

410
00:26:06,367 --> 00:26:09,400
But, I think I can see
an even bigger surprise.

411
00:26:10,133 --> 00:26:10,967
[CLEARS THROAT]

412
00:26:10,967 --> 00:26:12,467
- My god!
- [MARTIN] There we go!

413
00:26:12,467 --> 00:26:15,433
- The shock is blinding me!
- [JUSTIN] Luna?!

414
00:26:15,433 --> 00:26:17,367
- [ALL CLAPPING]
- Congrats!

415
00:26:17,367 --> 00:26:19,767
Oh, my god! Luna!

416
00:26:19,767 --> 00:26:23,333
Congratulations!
I'm so happy for you!

417
00:26:23,333 --> 00:26:26,233
Oh, I volunteer
to design the wedding gown!

418
00:26:26,233 --> 00:26:27,200
- Promise?
- For sure!

419
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:28,767
Can I be the maid of honor?

420
00:26:28,767 --> 00:26:30,200
Of course!

421
00:26:30,467 --> 00:26:31,500
[SMOOCHES]

422
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:32,767
- Bro.
- Hmm?

423
00:26:32,767 --> 00:26:34,200
[GIO] Will you be my best man?

424
00:26:34,567 --> 00:26:35,700
Of course, bro.

425
00:26:37,767 --> 00:26:38,767
[EDWARD] Okay, okay!

426
00:26:38,767 --> 00:26:40,400
[CHESKA] Congrats, Luna.

427
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:42,700
For an everlasting friendship.

428
00:26:42,733 --> 00:26:43,700
Cheers!

429
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:46,100
[ALL] Cheers!

430
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:47,767
[GLASSES CLINK]

431
00:26:48,467 --> 00:26:50,633
- Cheers, everyone!
- Congrats, congrats!

432
00:26:50,633 --> 00:26:51,667
Thank you!

433
00:26:51,667 --> 00:26:52,767
[CHUCKLES]

434
00:26:53,767 --> 00:27:00,700
["TADHANA" BY
SOFRONIO VASQUEZ PLAYING]

435
00:27:15,733 --> 00:27:22,700
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

436
00:27:37,733 --> 00:27:44,667
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

437
00:27:57,533 --> 00:28:02,667
[FOOTSTEPS THUDDING]

438
00:28:02,900 --> 00:28:04,333
[GIO] Hurry up, bro.

439
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:07,433
I'm just trying to be careful.

440
00:28:07,833 --> 00:28:09,433
It's so dark down here.

441
00:28:10,567 --> 00:28:12,533
We should've just called
a repairman.

442
00:28:12,533 --> 00:28:14,233
We can afford it now.

443
00:28:17,267 --> 00:28:18,700
[MARTIN]
We need to check first.

444
00:28:20,300 --> 00:28:22,267
This basement's been blown up.

445
00:28:22,533 --> 00:28:24,667
There's nothing left to check.

446
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:27,667
[TONGUE CLICKS]

447
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:29,300
You're right.

448
00:28:29,633 --> 00:28:32,467
We should've gotten
someone to fix it.

449
00:28:34,667 --> 00:28:41,633
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

450
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:49,400
Bro...

451
00:28:51,267 --> 00:28:52,267
Hm?

452
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:54,900
- What's that?
- Look at this.

453
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:00,933
[EXHALES]

454
00:29:05,333 --> 00:29:06,300
Gold...

455
00:29:06,867 --> 00:29:07,833
It's gold.

456
00:29:08,367 --> 00:29:11,400
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

457
00:29:12,667 --> 00:29:19,633
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

458
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:26,800
[CHUCKLING]

459
00:29:29,667 --> 00:29:33,633
[SOFT, DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

460
00:29:34,767 --> 00:29:35,967
[GIO CHUCKLES]

461
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:37,600
Martin!

462
00:29:41,300 --> 00:29:42,267
[MARTIN GASPS]

463
00:29:43,467 --> 00:29:44,900
I-it's the treasure.

464
00:29:44,900 --> 00:29:46,900
[LAUGHING] We found it!

465
00:29:46,900 --> 00:29:48,800
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

466
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:50,233
We're rich.

467
00:29:50,533 --> 00:29:52,633
We-- We're rich.

468
00:29:52,633 --> 00:29:55,900
[BOTH SCREAMING]
We're rich! We're rich!

469
00:29:55,900 --> 00:29:58,600
[CHEERING]

470
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,667
[GIO] Wait...

471
00:30:00,367 --> 00:30:02,633
- Let me see it again.
- [MARTIN] Move!

472
00:30:03,300 --> 00:30:05,633
[BOTH CHEERING]
